# Unity 6.5 Project Rules

## Project Overview

Universal Unity 6.5 template: URP, C# 12, **UniRx + UniTask + UI Toolkit** (no uGUI), **Cinemachine 3 + VFX Graph**, Unity feature packs, Cursor + MCP bootstrap on first open.

C# / MonoBehaviour: `unity-core.mdc`. Layout & asmdefs: `code-organization.mdc`. Agent behavior: `agent-guidelines.mdc`. MCP: `unity-mcp.mdc`.

## Tech Stack (default template)

- **Unity**: 6.5 (6000.5)
- **C#**: 12.0
- **Rendering**: URP 17.5 — `Settings/Rendering/RPAsset.asset`
- **Cameras**: Cinemachine 3.1 — `unity-cinemachine.mdc`
- **Effects**: VFX Graph 17.5 only — `unity-vfx.mdc` (no ParticleSystem in game content)
- **UI**: UI Toolkit only — `unity-ui.mdc`
- **Reactive**: UniRx (vendored, trimmed)
- **Async**: UniTask (pinned git); `Game.Core` uses `Awaitable` for bootstrap
- **Feature packs**: 2D, Characters+Animation, ECS (opt-in), Worldbuilding (ProBuilder)
- **MCP**: Coplay unity-mcp 10+ (stdio); Roslyn, ProBuilder, Cinemachine, VFX Graph, glTFast; optional **asset_gen** (AI 3D/2D, BYO keys)
- **Testing**: `Game.Tests`; MCP **testing** group when running tests

## Scenes

Bootstrap (build 0) → `GameManager` + `BootstrapSceneLoader` → **MainMenu** (build 1): Cinemachine rig, cinematic main menu (`MainMenuController`), level backdrop, `GameSession` / `GameplayReveal`. **Game** (build 2): gameplay (e.g. RobotPlayer) with Cinemachine + `GameplayCameraZoom`. VFX sample prefab is reference-only.

## Principles

- Prefer composition over singletons except bootstrap lifecycle (`GameManager`).
- UI bindings: always `UIBindingScope`.
- Do not add `com.unity.ugui` or `UnityEngine.UI`.
- Cameras via Cinemachine; effects via VFX Graph.

